This might have been taken as an expression of sor- row and devotion, or of weariness and hope of resting before long. Prince Vasili understood it as an expression of weariness. 
"And I?" he said; "do you think it is easier for me? I am as worn out as a post horse, but still I must have a talk with you, Catiche, a very serious talk."
